Robert Igara, the government's chief secretary, said the population in the area affected by the tsunami was 8,000 to 10,000 people.
Australia will provide transport for relief supplies and a mobile hospital to Papua New Guinea (PNG) following Friday's tsunami tragedy.
Authorities at Aitape in the West Sepik province, on Papua New Guinea's northwest coast, said the tsunami that hit the coast west of Aitape on Friday night had wiped out three villages and had almost completely destroyed another.
Australia said it will provide transport for relief supplies and a mobile hospital to Papua New Guinea.
